[0m[48;2;79;40;40m[39m- 136     [0m:[39m[48;2;36;25;28m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe problem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The prerequisites list VPC endpoints for Bedrock, S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs. KMS is not listed. If S3 uses SSE-KMS (as specified in the Encryption row), every S3 GetObject call to load prompt templates requires a KMS API call to decrypt the data key. Without a KMS VPC endpoint, Lambda in a private subnet cannot reach KMS and will fail with timeout or access errors when loading prompts from S3.[K
